<TITLE> HC orders 'status quo' at Botanical Garden, Zoo </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 2 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court Tuesday directed the government to maintain a four-week status quo on plans to set up a dredging pipeline through the National Botanical Garden and Dhaka Zoo. The bench of justice HM Shamsuddin and justice Borhanuddin also issued a rule nisi on the government asking it to explain in two weeks why the set up should not be declared illegal and harmful to the environment. The order was given on a petition filed by Human Rights and Peace of Bangladesh, a local NGO. Manzil Morshed, lawyer for the petitioner, told reporters that the environment ministry had given permission to a real estate developer to fill up a low lying area adjacent to the Botanical Garden and Dhaka Zoo and set up a dredging pipeline, which is a major threat to the environment. The secretaries to the environment and fisheries and livestock ministries and top officials of the Botanical Garden and Dhaka Zoo have been made respondents to the High Court directive and rule. b
